    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-03-08T02:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-03-08T02:00:00-05:00" n="571"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d571">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/4619: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China (<persName corresp="#p_JNT1" type="from"
                            >Johnson</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Shanghai</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-03-08T15:00:00+08:00"
                            >March 8, 1932—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received March 8—10:55 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your 80, March 7, noon [<hi rend="italic">12 p.m.</hi>]. With my British, French
                    and Italian colleagues and our respective commanders in chief we agreed
                    yesterday to pool our information regarding status of military operations and
                    have same forwarded to Geneva through British Minister as Senior Minister. This
                    information will be sent daily to Geneva from now on and serially numbered.
                    Situation report No. 1 was due today. Does the Department desire that I repeat
                    these reports to it?<note n="66" xml:id="d571fn66">In telegram No. 81, March 8,
                        5 p.m., the Department requested repetition of reports on the situation
                        referred to.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_JNT1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
